You only need to scan through the dataset with single pass and constant space, consider the following:
Image the matrix like an onion, with N layer of "rings", 
1. for each layer, locate four points at the corner, and and interchange the values of these four points;
2. move on to the points clockwise to them and do the same;; 
3. now you have reduced 1 layer and can move on to the next layer
4. recursively to solve the matrix with (n-2) dimension
* attached is the rust code

 ```
        let ml = matrix.len();
        let mut l_start = 0;
        let mut l_end = matrix.len() - 1;
        let mut n = matrix.len();

        while n > 1 {
            for offset in l_start..l_end {
                // i-th point starting from top left to right
                let a = matrix[l_start][offset];
                // i-th point starting from top right to bottom right
                let b = matrix[offset][l_end];
                // i-th point starting from bottom right to bottom left
                let c = matrix[l_end][(ml - 1) - offset];
                // i-th point starting from bottom left to upper left
                let d = matrix[(ml - 1) - offset][l_start];

                // swap the value
                matrix[l_start][offset] = d;
                matrix[offset][l_end] = a;
                matrix[l_end][ml - 1 - offset] = b;
                matrix[ml - 1 - offset][l_start] = c;
            }
            // decrement the dimension counter
            n -= 2;
            l_start += 1;
            l_end -= 1;
