The reason why memory is O(N) is because of the call-stack. The call-stack can get up to O(LOG(N)) Deep, however, we have head recursion. So, there will be One call at level 0, 2 calls at level 1, 4 calls at level 2, etc. This cancels out the logrithmic depth and we wind up right back with O(N) memory complexity.

