# Intuition
The code is an implementation of the Merge Sort algorithm for sorting a singly-linked list. The idea behind Merge Sort is to divide the list into two halves, recursively sort each half, and then merge the sorted halves to obtain the final sorted list.
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach

1. **'sortList' function:**

This function is the entry point for the sorting process.
If the list has one or zero elements (i.e., head is null or has only one node), it's already considered sorted, and the function returns the input list.
Otherwise, the list is divided into two halves using the get_mid function to find the middle node.
The sortList function is then recursively called on both halves to sort them.
Finally, the two sorted halves are merged using the mergeTwoLists function, and the merged result is returned.

2. **get_mid function:**

This function finds the middle node of the input list using the "slow and fast pointer" approach.
It maintains two pointers: midPrev and head.
While head and head.next are not null, the midPrev pointer is advanced one step at a time, and the head pointer is advanced two steps at a time.
This ensures that when head reaches the end of the list, midPrev points to the node just before the middle node.
The middle node is then detached from the rest of the list, and the function returns the middle node.

3. **mergeTwoLists function:**

This function merges two sorted linked lists into a single sorted linked list.
It uses a dummy head (dummyhead) and a tail pointer to build the merged list.
While both input lists (list1 and list2) are not empty, the function compares the values of the nodes at the front of both lists.
The smaller node is added to the merged list, and the corresponding pointer (list1 or list2) is advanced.
The tail pointer is also moved to the newly added node.
The process continues until one of the input lists becomes empty.
The remaining nodes in the non-empty list are then directly appended to the merged list.
Finally, the merged list is returned, excluding the initial dummy head.lin
