# Approach
First, we create a HashSet to store all the unique elements from our **nums** array. Once we've added the items to this set, we proceed to iterate through all the values in the range of **[1, nums.length]** to determine if they already exist in the set. If a value doesn't exist, we include it in an ArrayList of missing values. Finally, we return this ArrayList containing the missing values.

