We swap elements whose values aren't equal to their indices until we reach the end of the array, then return elements whose indices and values aren't equal.
```python
    def findDisappearedNumbers(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[int]:
        l = 0
        while l < len(nums):
            pos = nums[l]-1
            if nums[l] == nums[pos]:
                l += 1
            else:
                nums[l], nums[pos] = nums[pos], nums[l]
        return [i+1 for i,e in enumerate(nums) if i+1 != e]
